I grew up with the saying: Three is a crowd and more is a disaster. The importance of privacy and self respect with importance. However, we live in a social media era where everyone is entitled to your narrative. The minute you put yourself out to the public, they now own your life and that is dangerous. Many relationships have fallen on the way because of the third party, who comes in a form of social media in particular the DMs. Display Messaging as it is called is the messaging platform found on Instagram. The popular picture and video platform has now seen a growing trend in its messaging platform. More and more people are using this platform to text and communicate with another. This concept has opened the door to cheating and more and more people are being exposed for cheating on the platform. So how can you tame the DM beast?